THE APARTMENT JOB

4
00:00:57.056 --> 00:01:00.602
TRUE VALUE STATE
2025 BEST APARTMENT COMPLEX TO LIVE IN

5
00:01:33.259 --> 00:01:35.845
{\an8}LONG-TERM REPAIR RESERVE FUND
USED FOR FLOOR REPAIRS

6
00:01:50.735 --> 00:01:52.028
{\an8}The usual. right?

7
00:01:52.111 --> 00:01:52.946
{\an8}Thanks.

8
00:01:57.617 --> 00:01:59.369
HK TRADING AND INVESTMENT

9
00:02:02.997 --> 00:02:04.415
Good morning. sir.

10
00:02:13.967 --> 00:02:15.969
HK TRADING AND INVESTMENT
BREAK ROOM ACCESS VOUCHER

11
00:02:19.180 --> 00:02:20.306
Hello. sir.

12
00:02:21.975 --> 00:02:23.184
Good luck.

13
00:02:26.521 --> 00:02:28.231
Nothing special came up last night.

14
00:02:31.734 --> 00:02:32.902
This is bad.

15
00:02:34.654 --> 00:02:36.865
Let's just do it by ourselves.
Come on. let's begin.

16
00:02:38.199 --> 00:02:39.659
All right. let's do this.

17
00:02:40.451 --> 00:02:41.536
-Hold on.
-What's going on?

18
00:02:42.787 --> 00:02:44.247
-Show us your hand.
-Oh no.

19
00:02:50.253 --> 00:02:51.337
Hello. sir.

20
00:02:55.466 --> 00:02:56.384
This is good!

21
00:02:57.051 --> 00:02:57.969
I won!

22
00:03:04.475 --> 00:03:05.310
I only won once.

23
00:03:08.730 --> 00:03:09.731
-Twenty.
-Twenty.

24
00:03:16.738 --> 00:03:17.906
Hey. Mr. Park!

25
00:03:17.989 --> 00:03:19.908
Luck is on my side today.

26
00:03:19.991 --> 00:03:20.825
Thanks.

27
00:03:23.119 --> 00:03:24.370
He's here often these days.

28
00:03:25.163 --> 00:03:26.915
-The Lizard?
-"Lizard"?

29
00:03:27.582 --> 00:03:29.918
He's known for avoiding blame
and slipping away

30
00:03:30.001 --> 00:03:31.544
whenever a gambling den is raided.

31
00:03:32.378 --> 00:03:35.340
Let's see. Red. red…

32
00:03:35.423 --> 00:03:36.341
What does he do?

33
00:03:36.424 --> 00:03:38.217
He's an apartment facility manager.

34
00:03:38.718 --> 00:03:40.220
An apartment facility manager?

35
00:03:40.303 --> 00:03:41.971
Yes. but he's a VIP here.

36
00:03:42.055 --> 00:03:43.139
No unpaid debts either.

37
00:03:43.223 --> 00:03:44.182
It's two pair!

38
00:03:44.265 --> 00:03:46.059
A VIP facility manager…

39
00:03:46.142 --> 00:03:47.560
The job must pay pretty well.

40
00:03:47.644 --> 00:03:49.229
-Take good care of him.
-Yes. sir.

41
00:03:49.312 --> 00:03:50.605
And Mr. Oh is here.

42
00:03:50.688 --> 00:03:52.482
so we've made preparations
for your meeting.

43
00:03:52.565 --> 00:03:54.067
It's been a while.

44
00:03:54.567 --> 00:03:56.361
-Let's go see him. then.
-Yes. sir.

45
00:04:04.577 --> 00:04:07.288
Do you really have
a top-tier credit rating. Mr. Oh?

46
00:04:07.872 --> 00:04:09.207
Of course.

47
00:04:09.290 --> 00:04:12.710
They only accept members
with a Grade 1 credit rating.

48
00:04:12.794 --> 00:04:14.629
But your card loan interest rate is 19.9%.

49
00:04:15.880 --> 00:04:18.466
If you take out three card loans
and max out your cash advances.

50
00:04:18.549 --> 00:04:20.176
you should be able to pay us back.

51
00:04:20.260 --> 00:04:22.428
Mr. Park. I can pay you back

52
00:04:22.512 --> 00:04:23.888
once I sell my apartment.

53
00:04:23.972 --> 00:04:25.765
I'm telling you. I'm good for it.

54
00:04:25.848 --> 00:04:27.392
But that's not in Seoul.

55
00:04:27.475 --> 00:04:28.977
The housing market is dead out there.

56
00:04:29.060 --> 00:04:30.979
We don't know when it'll sell.

57
00:04:31.062 --> 00:04:32.480
What about the interest?

58
00:04:33.398 --> 00:04:35.817
We'll take out loans
with the personal info you provided

59
00:04:35.900 --> 00:04:37.151
when you got your access card.

60
00:04:37.235 --> 00:04:38.486
You'll get a verification code.

61
00:04:38.569 --> 00:04:40.488
Hey. you're really hurting my feelings.

62
00:04:40.571 --> 00:04:42.073
-How can you do this to me?
-Please stop.

63
00:04:43.616 --> 00:04:46.411
-Let go of me!
-Relax. You'll only hurt yourself.

64
00:04:50.581 --> 00:04:51.749
{\an8}FACE RECOGNITION FAILED

65
00:04:54.127 --> 00:04:55.545
Smile. Mr. Oh.

66
00:04:57.755 --> 00:04:59.257
NARA BANK CARD LOAN VERIFICATION CODE

67
00:04:59.966 --> 00:05:01.217
It's 236745.

68
00:05:04.095 --> 00:05:05.763
The loan went through.

69
00:05:05.847 --> 00:05:07.307
All right. Meeting's over.

70
00:05:09.726 --> 00:05:10.810
Sir.

71
00:05:10.893 --> 00:05:12.312
We got Mr. Choi's location.

72
00:05:12.395 --> 00:05:14.522
Really? Are the papers ready?

73
00:05:14.605 --> 00:05:17.233
-Yes. I printed everything.
-Okay. Let's go.

74
00:05:17.317 --> 00:05:18.151
Yes. sir.

75
00:05:20.903 --> 00:05:23.114
29TH ANNUAL NATIONAL YOUTH CONCERT

76
00:05:25.491 --> 00:05:27.035
CHOI YE-WON

77
00:05:35.501 --> 00:05:36.961
Mr. Choi is here.

78
00:05:41.841 --> 00:05:44.427
{\an8}-Stop right there!
-Get him!

79
00:05:44.510 --> 00:05:45.595
He's heading to the hall!

80
00:05:49.015 --> 00:05:49.974
Get him!

81
00:05:58.941 --> 00:06:00.068
Get him!

82
00:06:16.417 --> 00:06:17.418
You're late.

83
00:06:18.002 --> 00:06:20.171
-Your daughter's performance is over.
-Mr. Park.

84
00:06:20.254 --> 00:06:21.923
I'd like to speak with you in private.

85
00:06:22.507 --> 00:06:24.967
Don't come closer. I'm completely broke!

86
00:06:25.051 --> 00:06:26.302
What can you do about it?

87
00:06:32.892 --> 00:06:34.393
There is something I can do.

88
00:06:35.978 --> 00:06:36.854
Your fingerprint.

89
00:06:36.938 --> 00:06:38.106
What is this?

90
00:06:38.689 --> 00:06:40.817
I checked your dormant bank accounts.

91
00:06:40.900 --> 00:06:43.402
You had about three million won.
I bet you didn't know.

92
00:06:43.486 --> 00:06:45.446
Stamp the paper
to authorize the withdrawal.

93
00:06:50.952 --> 00:06:51.786
And cancellation papers

94
00:06:51.869 --> 00:06:54.539
for the life insurance policy
your wife took out.

95
00:06:55.832 --> 00:06:57.792
You look surprised. Didn't you know?

96
00:06:57.875 --> 00:06:58.835
No.

97
00:06:58.918 --> 00:07:01.295
We're canceling it anyway.
so live a long life. Go on.

98
00:07:07.009 --> 00:07:09.303
We also looked into the land
your ancestors had.

99
00:07:09.387 --> 00:07:10.471
My ancestors?

100
00:07:10.555 --> 00:07:13.224
Your great-grandfather's land
was taken by the government.

101
00:07:13.307 --> 00:07:15.351
and some compensation money
was never claimed.

102
00:07:15.435 --> 00:07:16.936
That would be enough

103
00:07:17.019 --> 00:07:18.729
to clear the debt

104
00:07:18.813 --> 00:07:19.939
you owe me.

105
00:07:24.277 --> 00:07:25.695
LOSS COMPENSATION AGREEMENT

106
00:07:32.368 --> 00:07:33.703
-Big Guy.
-Yes. sir.

107
00:07:33.786 --> 00:07:35.246
Give it to him.

108
00:07:40.751 --> 00:07:42.295
Don't skip your meals.

109
00:07:43.254 --> 00:07:45.715
{\an8}HK TRADING AND INVESTMENT
BREAK ROOM ACCESS VOUCHER

110
00:07:45.798 --> 00:07:47.175
Oh. come on.

111
00:07:47.675 --> 00:07:50.178
Please help me. Mr. Park!

112
00:07:50.261 --> 00:07:52.305
Your guests have been waiting a long time.

113
00:07:53.347 --> 00:07:54.182
Get ready.

114
00:07:54.807 --> 00:07:56.976
No!

115
00:07:57.059 --> 00:07:58.352
Everything you own is ours!

116
00:07:58.436 --> 00:08:00.646
-Catch that bastard!
-Mr. Choi!

117
00:08:03.858 --> 00:08:05.109
Get him!

118
00:08:15.203 --> 00:08:16.287
Wow.

119
00:08:16.954 --> 00:08:19.373
I can't believe
you even looked into his ancestors' land.

120
00:08:19.457 --> 00:08:20.791
You really are amazing. sir.

121
00:08:20.875 --> 00:08:22.627
I can dig up anything.

122
00:08:23.920 --> 00:08:26.547
Making threats even before digging
is for amateurs.

123
00:08:33.429 --> 00:08:35.473
15TH ANNUAL CHILDREN'S FIELD DAY

124
00:09:48.504 --> 00:09:49.589
First place!

125
00:09:56.220 --> 00:09:59.515
It was my first time hiring someone
for the role. so I was worried.

126
00:09:59.599 --> 00:10:01.475
But you even won first place. Thank you.

127
00:10:01.559 --> 00:10:02.476
It was nothing.

128
00:10:02.560 --> 00:10:03.686
I added a little extra.

129
00:10:04.937 --> 00:10:07.815
I'll always try my best
to satisfy my customers.

130
00:10:08.399 --> 00:10:10.443
Call me when there's another event.

131
00:10:10.526 --> 00:10:12.528
-I'll give you a 10% discount.
-All right.

132
00:10:13.362 --> 00:10:14.530
Thank you for today.

133
00:10:15.031 --> 00:10:16.699
-Bye. then.
-Goodbye.

134
00:10:26.792 --> 00:10:27.710
Yes!

135
00:10:31.339 --> 00:10:32.882
My goodness.

136
00:10:32.965 --> 00:10:35.760
It was way too obvious
that you weren't her mom.

137
00:10:35.843 --> 00:10:37.720
You didn't even look at the kid.

138
00:10:37.803 --> 00:10:39.930
Running fast isn't the point. you know.

139
00:10:40.014 --> 00:10:41.766
Think about your customer's needs.

140
00:10:41.849 --> 00:10:43.184
Let's be professional. okay?

141
00:10:43.267 --> 00:10:44.727
I know you're good at this. Ha-ri.

142
00:10:44.810 --> 00:10:46.729
Hey. I won first place.

143
00:10:46.812 --> 00:10:50.149
I made her feel proud
that her mom was the fastest runner.

144
00:10:50.232 --> 00:10:52.068
I left her with a great memory.

145
00:10:52.151 --> 00:10:53.903
How long are you going to live like this?

146
00:10:56.864 --> 00:10:57.990
For a while. at least.

147
00:10:58.824 --> 00:11:01.035
So you'll keep sending me gigs. won't you?

148
00:11:01.118 --> 00:11:04.330
Why did you have to lie
and say you got a job at a law firm?

149
00:11:04.413 --> 00:11:06.540
You said your sister manages your salary.

150
00:11:06.624 --> 00:11:10.127
You're going to have to keep faking
a salary you don't have.

151
00:11:10.211 --> 00:11:12.713
Why in the world did you lie
about passing the bar exam?

152
00:11:12.797 --> 00:11:15.508
I never lied about passing the bar.

153
00:11:16.092 --> 00:11:17.802
I just never told her that I failed.

154
00:11:19.095 --> 00:11:20.054
Whatever.

155
00:11:20.137 --> 00:11:23.474
Just tell your sister the truth
before this gets out of hand.

156
00:11:23.557 --> 00:11:24.809
You could get in huge trouble.

157
00:11:31.148 --> 00:11:33.859
Choi Woo-shik says this
to Song Kang-ho in <i>Parasite.</i>

158
00:11:33.943 --> 00:11:36.946
"Father. I don't consider this fraud
or any kind of crime.

159
00:11:37.029 --> 00:11:39.407
because I'm going to get into
this university next year."

160
00:11:40.783 --> 00:11:43.327
Ha-jeong. I'm going to pass next year--

161
00:11:43.411 --> 00:11:44.286
Kang Ha-ri.

162
00:12:03.305 --> 00:12:04.390
What?

163
00:12:06.684 --> 00:12:08.644
What is it?

164
00:12:10.187 --> 00:12:11.647
Don't you have something to tell me?

165
00:12:12.940 --> 00:12:15.276
<i>This is it.</i>
<i>I'm going to tell her the truth.</i>

166
00:12:19.363 --> 00:12:21.449
Ha-jeong. I…

167
00:12:22.908 --> 00:12:24.118
To be honest…

168
00:12:24.201 --> 00:12:26.036
I knew it. Look.

169
00:12:26.120 --> 00:12:28.873
You stole my clothes
and were playing dumb?

170
00:12:29.373 --> 00:12:33.043
We're completely different sizes.
Why would you wear such huge clothes?

171
00:12:33.127 --> 00:12:35.838
Don't you know
oversized clothing is trendy?

172
00:12:35.921 --> 00:12:38.507
This is fashion. You're just clueless.

173
00:12:43.554 --> 00:12:44.638
What's this?

174
00:12:46.390 --> 00:12:48.851
What? Hérzina?

175
00:12:49.351 --> 00:12:52.271
This must've cost a fortune.

176
00:12:52.354 --> 00:12:54.064
Hey. you're a lawyer now.

177
00:12:54.148 --> 00:12:57.985
You should have at least one suit
that fits you properly.

178
00:13:01.322 --> 00:13:04.950
Ha-jeong.
you really didn't need to buy this.

179
00:13:05.034 --> 00:13:06.202
Pay me back. then.

180
00:13:06.827 --> 00:13:08.370
Your tuition and your clothes.

181
00:13:08.454 --> 00:13:11.207
I'm charging 19% interest on it. Got that?

182
00:13:12.958 --> 00:13:15.503
What kind of sister
charges loan-shark rates?

183
00:13:16.170 --> 00:13:17.254
Kang Ha-jeong!

184
00:13:34.980 --> 00:13:37.066
Excuse me. Coming through.

185
00:13:38.651 --> 00:13:39.568
Excuse me.

186
00:13:40.569 --> 00:13:41.862
Attorney Kim. it's going down.

187
00:13:41.946 --> 00:13:43.197
It's going down.

188
00:13:45.741 --> 00:13:47.284
<i>B3.</i>

189
00:13:49.870 --> 00:13:52.456
WEE PARTNERS
FREE LEGAL CONSULTATION

190
00:13:52.540 --> 00:13:53.541
Hello.

191
00:13:55.084 --> 00:13:56.377
FREE LEGAL CONSULTANTS

192
00:13:59.672 --> 00:14:00.631
Oh. wow.

193
00:14:01.423 --> 00:14:03.509
You're dressed like a lawyer today.

194
00:14:04.176 --> 00:14:05.094
You look cool.

195
00:14:06.178 --> 00:14:07.555
Thank you.

196
00:14:09.098 --> 00:14:10.975
Is that something to be grateful for?

197
00:14:21.360 --> 00:14:24.071
CONSULTANT KANG HA-RI
SEXUAL ASSAULT. INJURY. DEFAMATION. FRAUD

198
00:14:32.246 --> 00:14:33.914
Hanging in there. Mr. Park?

199
00:14:33.998 --> 00:14:35.165
I'm fine!

200
00:14:38.127 --> 00:14:40.170
Just look at him go.

201
00:14:44.425 --> 00:14:45.801
We're almost there.

202
00:14:45.885 --> 00:14:47.428
Let's stay strong. everyone!

203
00:14:50.890 --> 00:14:52.892
You must be quite hungry.

204
00:14:53.559 --> 00:14:55.561
It's not much.
but I put something together.

205
00:14:55.644 --> 00:14:56.812
You made these yourself?

206
00:14:56.896 --> 00:14:57.938
Of course.

207
00:14:59.023 --> 00:15:01.775
SEOUL METROPOLITAN POLICE AGENCY
CHIEF OF INVESTIGATION. SON DAE-UN

208
00:15:01.859 --> 00:15:02.818
This is good!

209
00:15:03.402 --> 00:15:04.862
You could open a restaurant.

210
00:15:04.945 --> 00:15:06.322
KOREA'S FINEST EEL CUISINE

211
00:15:06.405 --> 00:15:08.240
-Customer number 256!
-That's me.

212
00:15:08.324 --> 00:15:09.491
Here's your food. sir.

213
00:15:09.575 --> 00:15:10.784
Thank you.

214
00:15:10.868 --> 00:15:14.288
<i>Of course it's good. It's premium eel</i>
<i>from the most famous spot in Gangnam.</i>

215
00:15:14.371 --> 00:15:16.415
Mr. Park can do anything.

216
00:15:16.498 --> 00:15:18.792
He even booked tickets
to a Lim Young-woong concert

217
00:15:18.876 --> 00:15:20.711
when no one else could.

218
00:15:23.297 --> 00:15:25.466
<i>I had to use a bot to score a reservation.</i>

219
00:15:26.216 --> 00:15:27.509
Okay!

220
00:15:28.260 --> 00:15:31.055
He even got us
a limited-edition luxury bag

221
00:15:31.138 --> 00:15:34.266
that my wife was desperate
to get her hands on.

222
00:15:35.100 --> 00:15:35.935
HÉRZINA WAITING LINE

223
00:15:36.810 --> 00:15:39.980
<i>I lined up at the department store</i>
<i>at 4 a.m. for this.</i>

224
00:15:41.357 --> 00:15:43.275
It's all thanks to you.

225
00:15:43.359 --> 00:15:45.819
I even made some dessert for you.

226
00:15:45.903 --> 00:15:47.154
Sir.

227
00:15:48.197 --> 00:15:49.698
-And for you.
-Right.

228
00:15:49.782 --> 00:15:51.325
And my first gift to you. sir.

229
00:15:51.992 --> 00:15:53.577
You really didn't have to.

230
00:15:53.661 --> 00:15:54.745
Here you go. sir.

231
00:15:57.122 --> 00:16:01.335
I always prepare high-quality food
that won't upset your stomach.

232
00:16:05.506 --> 00:16:07.007
I shouldn't smoke.

233
00:16:07.883 --> 00:16:10.260
but it's impossible not to
with this amazing view.

234
00:16:12.179 --> 00:16:13.931
But I don't have a lighter.

235
00:16:16.058 --> 00:16:17.142
You all quit. right?

236
00:16:17.226 --> 00:16:18.894
-Yes.
-Yes. we all quit.

237
00:16:21.146 --> 00:16:23.983
Too bad. This is my last one.
I can't just throw it away.

238
00:16:26.694 --> 00:16:28.278
I'll go grab it.

239
00:16:36.870 --> 00:16:39.957
You're like a pro badminton player.
Ms. Kim.

240
00:16:41.500 --> 00:16:44.128
-I've improved a lot thanks to you.
-I can see that.

241
00:16:46.171 --> 00:16:47.589
My goodness.

242
00:16:49.174 --> 00:16:50.217
My father

243
00:16:51.051 --> 00:16:54.054
was great at hitting and smashing things
back in the day.

244
00:16:55.556 --> 00:16:59.268
No wonder. He's extremely skilled.

245
00:17:00.060 --> 00:17:02.730
But are you his son. then?

246
00:17:02.813 --> 00:17:05.524
Yes. I'm his son. Park Hae-kang.

247
00:17:05.607 --> 00:17:06.567
Nice to meet you.

248
00:17:06.650 --> 00:17:07.776
Goodness.

249
00:17:07.860 --> 00:17:10.696
You're handsome. just like your father.

250
00:17:13.032 --> 00:17:16.285
I don't resemble him.
but I am quite handsome.

251
00:17:25.627 --> 00:17:27.546
You're taking your meds. aren't you?

252
00:17:27.629 --> 00:17:29.131
This is better than medicine.

253
00:17:29.214 --> 00:17:30.883
This is really good spring water.

254
00:17:31.383 --> 00:17:34.053
You should be taking your meds.

255
00:17:34.136 --> 00:17:36.555
You'll die if you don't take them.

256
00:17:36.638 --> 00:17:40.350
I'm saying this for your sake. Boss.
Not mine.

257
00:17:40.434 --> 00:17:41.643
This is nice.

258
00:17:41.727 --> 00:17:43.854
You'll really die
if you don't take care of yourself.

259
00:17:43.937 --> 00:17:44.897
Are you kidding me?

260
00:17:45.773 --> 00:17:47.900
Are you challenging me
now that I'm retired?

261
00:17:48.400 --> 00:17:49.818
You want some hitting and smashing?

262
00:17:50.903 --> 00:17:52.988
I'm just worried about you. That's all.

263
00:17:53.072 --> 00:17:54.490
I won't die.

264
00:17:54.573 --> 00:17:55.532
What if you do?

265
00:17:56.158 --> 00:17:59.995
I won't die until I spend
all the money you keep sending me.

266
00:18:00.079 --> 00:18:03.040
But you sent a lot this month.

267
00:18:03.791 --> 00:18:05.084
Why did you give me so much?

268
00:18:05.167 --> 00:18:07.211
Well. you're the owner of the business.

269
00:18:07.294 --> 00:18:08.504
It's only natural.

270
00:18:08.587 --> 00:18:10.881
Still. I'm just the figurehead.

271
00:18:10.964 --> 00:18:13.175
You're supposed to give
the figurehead a cut.

272
00:18:13.258 --> 00:18:14.468
It would be rude not to.

273
00:18:14.551 --> 00:18:17.304
Right. We shouldn't live like thugs.

274
00:18:17.387 --> 00:18:18.263
But…

275
00:18:19.681 --> 00:18:21.517
how long will you run that gambling den?

276
00:18:23.185 --> 00:18:25.479
It's not easy to manage it.
and it's dangerous.

277
00:18:25.562 --> 00:18:28.607
Save what you're giving me
and help the others settle down.

278
00:18:28.690 --> 00:18:29.942
You make a clean break too.

279
00:18:30.025 --> 00:18:31.610
You've made enough money now.

280
00:18:31.693 --> 00:18:33.320
What are you talking about?

281
00:18:33.821 --> 00:18:36.990
After greasing everyone's palms.
there's nothing left.

282
00:18:37.074 --> 00:18:38.158
Plus.

283
00:18:38.659 --> 00:18:42.371
I have to earn a lot more
to help the guys follow their own paths.

284
00:18:42.454 --> 00:18:43.455
What about you?

285
00:18:44.581 --> 00:18:46.250
Is there anything you want to do?

286
00:18:46.959 --> 00:18:49.711
Gyeong-nam. Je-gil. and Big Guy.

287
00:18:50.337 --> 00:18:52.840
They all have dreams.
even if they may be small.

288
00:18:54.133 --> 00:18:55.175
Dreams?

289
00:18:57.719 --> 00:18:59.805
I don't have anything like that.

290
00:19:04.935 --> 00:19:06.311
Make sure to take your meds.

291
00:19:06.895 --> 00:19:10.065
You'd better not die on me. Or else I'll…

292
00:19:12.067 --> 00:19:13.360
-You little brat!
-Geez.

293
00:19:16.655 --> 00:19:17.656
You're still swift.

294
00:19:18.532 --> 00:19:19.825
Bring it on. you punk!

295
00:19:20.659 --> 00:19:22.327
I can't even see your hands.

296
00:19:22.411 --> 00:19:24.163
-You're too quick.
-Gosh…

297
00:19:25.873 --> 00:19:26.707
Let go of me!

298
00:19:26.790 --> 00:19:27.916
I'm not leaving.

299
00:19:28.000 --> 00:19:30.878
Lend me some money!

300
00:19:32.129 --> 00:19:34.006
Why can't you lend me money?

301
00:19:34.089 --> 00:19:36.216
Is his credit still top-tier?

302
00:19:36.300 --> 00:19:38.302
He's become our VVIP.

303
00:19:39.011 --> 00:19:39.928
Hang on.

304
00:19:40.554 --> 00:19:41.680
What?

305
00:19:41.763 --> 00:19:44.641
Mr. Park! Perfect timing.

306
00:19:44.725 --> 00:19:46.935
These assholes…

307
00:19:47.019 --> 00:19:48.478
-They won't listen--
-Sir.

308
00:19:49.146 --> 00:19:51.023
When did you become our VVIP?

309
00:19:51.607 --> 00:19:52.858
Hurry up and lend it to him.

310
00:19:55.360 --> 00:19:56.403
I knew it.

311
00:19:56.486 --> 00:19:59.823
Things get done quickly
when I talk to the boss directly.

312
00:19:59.907 --> 00:20:01.158
Did you hear…

313
00:20:02.576 --> 00:20:04.870
You jerk. Why are you giving me that look?

314
00:20:04.953 --> 00:20:05.996
Hey.

315
00:20:06.079 --> 00:20:08.916
I can pay back everything
if I just work for a week

316
00:20:08.999 --> 00:20:10.459
at my apartment complex.

317
00:20:10.542 --> 00:20:12.628
Don't look down on me.

318
00:20:14.546 --> 00:20:15.714
-Lend him the money.
-Yes. sir.

319
00:20:15.797 --> 00:20:17.966
I'll see you again. sir.

320
00:20:19.426 --> 00:20:20.886
Thank you. Mr. Park.

321
00:20:20.969 --> 00:20:24.806
-I'll work really hard.
-Let's go.

322
00:20:24.890 --> 00:20:26.975
You're all dead!

323
00:20:27.059 --> 00:20:29.394
Just you wait! Let go of me.
Don't carry me…

324
00:20:29.478 --> 00:20:31.230
Make sure we get
the money back right away.

325
00:20:31.313 --> 00:20:33.148
-I've got a bad feeling about this.
-Yes. sir.

326
00:20:39.947 --> 00:20:40.906
-Yun-seo.
-Yes?

327
00:20:40.989 --> 00:20:42.824
Is the representative election
notice ready?

328
00:20:42.908 --> 00:20:45.202
I'm just editing the text.
It's almost ready.

329
00:20:45.285 --> 00:20:46.161
-Okay.
-Right.

330
00:20:46.245 --> 00:20:48.247
Don't put so much work into it.
Nobody cares.

331
00:20:49.957 --> 00:20:51.041
Sang-tae.

332
00:20:51.833 --> 00:20:55.712
Shouldn't we do our best to make sure
our residents pay more attention?

333
00:20:55.796 --> 00:20:57.673
We should make announcements every day.

334
00:20:57.756 --> 00:20:59.716
Right. Sorry.

335
00:21:09.893 --> 00:21:11.770
Ha-jeong.

336
00:21:13.230 --> 00:21:15.315
We'd like you to keep doing

337
00:21:15.399 --> 00:21:17.234
that job for us.

338
00:21:19.736 --> 00:21:21.571
I told you. I can't.

339
00:21:21.655 --> 00:21:23.740
I said I'd stop when my sister got a job.

340
00:21:24.616 --> 00:21:25.867
Ha-jeong.

341
00:21:25.951 --> 00:21:28.996
Your sister's situation
is separate from yours.

342
00:21:30.163 --> 00:21:31.832
I'm sorry. sir.

343
00:21:31.915 --> 00:21:33.375
I really can't keep doing it.

344
00:21:34.042 --> 00:21:37.504
I've told you many times
that you won't get in any trouble.

345
00:21:42.175 --> 00:21:45.137
Mr. Choi! Can you come out here for a bit?

346
00:21:45.220 --> 00:21:46.471
Mr. Choi.

347
00:21:46.555 --> 00:21:49.558
Can you please tell me what's going on?

348
00:21:49.641 --> 00:21:51.643
How can floor repairs

349
00:21:51.727 --> 00:21:53.395
cost 365 million…

350
00:21:53.478 --> 00:21:55.647
Oh my gosh. This is insane.

351
00:21:55.731 --> 00:21:58.025
Three hundred million won
is actually a bargain.

352
00:21:58.108 --> 00:21:59.568
Bargain or not.

353
00:21:59.651 --> 00:22:02.946
the construction company
should be taking care of this.

354
00:22:03.030 --> 00:22:05.365
Why would you repair this
with the residents' money?

355
00:22:05.449 --> 00:22:07.451
Who said you could use
the repair reserve fund?

356
00:22:08.285 --> 00:22:10.495
This is exactly
what the repair reserve fund is for.

357
00:22:10.579 --> 00:22:15.000
You shouldn't spend it freely
just because it isn't your money.

358
00:22:15.083 --> 00:22:17.002
I'm so thirsty.
Give me something to drink.

359
00:22:17.085 --> 00:22:19.087
It's not my money.

360
00:22:19.171 --> 00:22:21.965
but I'm spending it appropriately
for the right purposes.

361
00:22:22.049 --> 00:22:24.134
That's my job.

362
00:22:24.217 --> 00:22:25.427
Mr. Choi.

363
00:22:25.510 --> 00:22:27.888
When spending such a large amount.

364
00:22:27.971 --> 00:22:30.474
you should get
the residents' approval first.

365
00:22:30.557 --> 00:22:31.683
Well…

366
00:22:32.893 --> 00:22:34.227
This was an urgent matter.

367
00:22:34.311 --> 00:22:36.772
Urgent? Did the floors
crumble down or what?

368
00:22:36.855 --> 00:22:38.065
Don't be ridiculous.

369
00:22:38.148 --> 00:22:39.649
Ms. Jang. you're so…

370
00:22:41.693 --> 00:22:43.945
invested in the complex's affairs.

371
00:22:44.696 --> 00:22:46.573
Of course. I am.

372
00:22:48.158 --> 00:22:49.201
Hello. everyone.

373
00:22:49.284 --> 00:22:50.535
You're here.

374
00:22:51.369 --> 00:22:53.121
-Hello.
-Hello.

375
00:22:53.622 --> 00:22:55.165
-Hello.
-Hello. sir.

376
00:22:55.248 --> 00:22:56.374
Hello.

377
00:22:56.458 --> 00:22:58.335
I received these as a gift.

378
00:22:58.418 --> 00:23:01.838
but I couldn't eat them all by myself.
so I thought I should share.

379
00:23:01.922 --> 00:23:04.091
Oh. you didn't have to. Thank you so much.

380
00:23:04.174 --> 00:23:05.008
Thank you.

381
00:23:06.718 --> 00:23:08.386
Thank you for always thinking of us.

382
00:23:08.470 --> 00:23:10.388
I'm just glad you all enjoy it.

383
00:23:10.472 --> 00:23:11.765
Let me get you some coffee.

384
00:23:11.848 --> 00:23:14.643
It's fine. I was only dropping by.

385
00:23:14.726 --> 00:23:16.978
You must be busy. I'll get going now.

386
00:23:22.400 --> 00:23:23.360
You're quite the beauty.

387
00:23:25.946 --> 00:23:26.780
Oh my.

388
00:23:27.614 --> 00:23:29.491
-Me?
-Goodbye.

389
00:23:29.574 --> 00:23:31.243
-Goodbye.
-You heard that. right?

390
00:23:31.326 --> 00:23:33.203
He said I'm quite the beauty.

391
00:23:48.760 --> 00:23:51.096
{\an8}PINE TREE FARM
TAEGOWON

392
00:24:07.028 --> 00:24:08.321
Up we go.

393
00:24:16.621 --> 00:24:17.747
Goodness.

394
00:24:18.999 --> 00:24:20.375
-Hello.
-Hello.

395
00:24:20.458 --> 00:24:22.586
SENIOR SECRETARY FOR CIVIL AFFAIRS
SONG U-SIK

396
00:24:22.669 --> 00:24:24.588
PROSECUTOR GENERAL
CHOI SEUNG-HO

397
00:24:24.671 --> 00:24:25.797
How have you been?

398
00:24:25.881 --> 00:24:28.008
SUPREME COURT JUSTICE
YOO GWANG-HO

399
00:24:28.091 --> 00:24:29.634
PRESIDENT OF GONGYEONG DAILY
LEE SANG-GYU

400
00:24:37.517 --> 00:24:41.438
I sent Mr. Kim a bonsai tree.

401
00:24:42.272 --> 00:24:43.106
What?

402
00:24:43.190 --> 00:24:46.985
You already got Mr. Kim acquitted
and made him a presidential candidate.

403
00:24:47.068 --> 00:24:48.403
Why would you send him that?

404
00:24:48.486 --> 00:24:49.321
He's right.

405
00:24:49.946 --> 00:24:53.241
Our newspaper took plenty of heat
covering for Mr. Kim too.

406
00:24:53.325 --> 00:24:54.951
Just thinking about it makes me…

407
00:24:55.535 --> 00:24:59.623
I just wanted him to see
the evergreen pine all year long

408
00:24:59.706 --> 00:25:00.624
and remember

409
00:25:01.208 --> 00:25:05.045
that we'll make him the president.
no matter what.

410
00:25:06.546 --> 00:25:10.550
Mr. Song. do you think
Mr. Kim really has a chance?

411
00:25:10.634 --> 00:25:13.386
Right now. he's the most likely candidate.

412
00:25:14.346 --> 00:25:16.431
"Most likely" isn't enough.

413
00:25:19.434 --> 00:25:22.062
We've spent a fortune on him so far.

414
00:25:22.145 --> 00:25:25.232
We need him to win
the presidency this time

415
00:25:25.815 --> 00:25:26.983
so it doesn't go to waste.

416
00:25:27.567 --> 00:25:30.195
And I'm certain
you'll all make sure that it happens.

417
00:25:32.030 --> 00:25:33.823
-Gosh.
-Of course.

418
00:25:33.907 --> 00:25:34.908
Thank you in advance.

419
00:25:34.991 --> 00:25:36.159
Of course.

420
00:25:57.138 --> 00:25:58.556
You're here.

421
00:25:59.432 --> 00:26:00.684
It wasn't hard to find. was it?

422
00:26:01.601 --> 00:26:02.644
Say hello.

423
00:26:03.311 --> 00:26:06.231
He's been eager to join our club.

424
00:26:06.731 --> 00:26:08.108
Nice to meet you.

425
00:26:08.608 --> 00:26:10.151
I'm Kwak Ju-gwon.

426
00:26:11.945 --> 00:26:13.405
-The police commissioner?
-Yes.

427
00:26:13.488 --> 00:26:18.451
He spent nearly 30 years
in public service. climbing the ranks.

428
00:26:19.035 --> 00:26:20.662
I begged Mr. Song here

429
00:26:20.745 --> 00:26:23.540
to let me meet you all.

430
00:26:25.750 --> 00:26:27.127
Justice Yoo.

431
00:26:27.877 --> 00:26:30.213
Your rulings showed consideration
for the underprivileged

432
00:26:30.297 --> 00:26:32.465
and protected
the people's fundamental rights.

433
00:26:33.049 --> 00:26:35.093
I really admire you. sir.

434
00:26:37.220 --> 00:26:38.638
The president of Gongyeong Daily.

435
00:26:38.722 --> 00:26:40.724
You stood firm against media censorship.

436
00:26:41.349 --> 00:26:42.183
I truly admire you.

437
00:26:47.856 --> 00:26:51.276
And our Prosecutor General.
who led the charge for reform.

438
00:26:51.359 --> 00:26:53.278
You really are my role model…

439
00:26:53.361 --> 00:26:54.404
Hey. cop.

440
00:26:56.573 --> 00:26:58.158
Are you at a fan meet or what?

441
00:26:59.117 --> 00:26:59.951
Pardon?

442
00:27:00.035 --> 00:27:02.454
This isn't a social gathering.

443
00:27:03.330 --> 00:27:06.082
Didn't the Senior Secretary tell you that?

444
00:27:06.166 --> 00:27:08.126
I was going to…

445
00:27:19.262 --> 00:27:20.513
Look at that. huh?

446
00:27:21.181 --> 00:27:23.058
But not anyone can join us. you know.

447
00:27:23.683 --> 00:27:25.393
Yes. I know. That's why I--

448
00:27:25.477 --> 00:27:26.519
Ten billion!

449
00:27:29.481 --> 00:27:30.565
Do you have ten billion won?

450
00:27:30.648 --> 00:27:31.649
Excuse me?

451
00:27:31.733 --> 00:27:35.653
The people here
are worth more than ten billion won.

452
00:27:35.737 --> 00:27:37.614
If you want to join our One Club.

453
00:27:38.323 --> 00:27:39.407
bring ten billion

454
00:27:39.491 --> 00:27:40.700
for the membership fee.

455
00:27:41.201 --> 00:27:42.786
That's the least you can do.

456
00:27:44.537 --> 00:27:48.792
I've explained the membership requirement.
so please head back safely.

457
00:27:59.386 --> 00:28:00.303
<i>Ten billion won?</i>

458
00:28:07.477 --> 00:28:08.520
That's what he said.

459
00:28:09.521 --> 00:28:11.523
The membership fee is ten billion won.

460
00:28:11.606 --> 00:28:13.650
Ten billion for a membership?

461
00:28:15.276 --> 00:28:16.903
That makes no sense.

462
00:28:18.196 --> 00:28:20.740
Nothing makes sense in this country.

463
00:28:21.658 --> 00:28:24.035
If the most powerful people in Korea
want ten billion.

464
00:28:24.536 --> 00:28:25.495
then ten billion it is.

465
00:28:27.914 --> 00:28:29.082
What will you do then?

466
00:28:32.669 --> 00:28:36.881
You know that I didn't climb this high

467
00:28:36.965 --> 00:28:38.091
by playing clean.

468
00:28:38.675 --> 00:28:40.260
I built a few connections

469
00:28:40.343 --> 00:28:43.012
and took some money.

470
00:28:44.597 --> 00:28:46.766
But thinking back now.

471
00:28:49.185 --> 00:28:52.105
I wonder if I should have been
even more corrupt.

472
00:28:53.398 --> 00:28:55.024
Even if I scrape together everything.

473
00:28:56.776 --> 00:28:58.236
it's hardly two billion.

474
00:28:58.737 --> 00:29:00.280
I need eight billion more.

475
00:29:00.363 --> 00:29:01.197
Sir.

476
00:29:05.577 --> 00:29:08.329
Why would you gather that money yourself?

477
00:29:09.998 --> 00:29:11.040
What?

478
00:29:13.376 --> 00:29:15.795
Squeeze it out of someone
who can't make a peep

479
00:29:15.879 --> 00:29:17.172
as you bleed them dry.

480
00:29:19.841 --> 00:29:21.801
That's impossible nowadays.

481
00:29:21.885 --> 00:29:23.511
There's someone perfect for that.

482
00:29:24.971 --> 00:29:28.475
Someone named Park Hae-kang.
who can do just about anything.

483
00:29:29.142 --> 00:29:30.351
Who is this guy?

484
00:29:31.561 --> 00:29:33.688
{\an8}<i>He runs a gambling den like a business.</i>

485
00:29:33.772 --> 00:29:37.442
{\an8}<i>He's ruthless when it comes to making</i>
<i>and collecting money.</i>

486
00:29:38.276 --> 00:29:39.110
{\an8}Come in.

487
00:29:41.237 --> 00:29:43.364
Mr. Park. you have a visitor.

488
00:29:45.909 --> 00:29:47.035
Mr. Son.

489
00:29:47.118 --> 00:29:49.621
What's the occasion? You didn't call.

490
00:29:50.330 --> 00:29:52.665
Your office sure is nice. Mr. Park.

491
00:29:53.708 --> 00:29:55.335
You've succeeded.

492
00:29:55.835 --> 00:29:58.838
Succeeded? I still have a long way to go.

493
00:30:00.924 --> 00:30:03.510
But what brings you here all of a sudden?

494
00:30:03.593 --> 00:30:05.762
I know you can pull off anything.

495
00:30:05.845 --> 00:30:08.473
At least. from what I've seen so far.

496
00:30:09.599 --> 00:30:11.643
-What is this about?
-Ten billion won.

497
00:30:12.727 --> 00:30:14.687
Get me ten billion won.

498
00:30:17.273 --> 00:30:18.107
Ten billion?

499
00:30:22.445 --> 00:30:24.155
What kind of scary joke is this?

500
00:30:26.950 --> 00:30:27.784
Sir.

501
00:30:28.660 --> 00:30:31.162
Have I done something wrong?

502
00:30:31.996 --> 00:30:33.873
If I have. please forgive me.

503
00:30:33.957 --> 00:30:35.917
-From now on--
-I'm not joking.

504
00:30:36.626 --> 00:30:38.503
Just think of it as paying it all up front

505
00:30:38.586 --> 00:30:41.130
instead of paying in installments
your whole life.

506
00:30:43.341 --> 00:30:47.136
How could I possibly have that much money?
Let alone in cash.

507
00:30:47.220 --> 00:30:48.263
Mr. Park.

508
00:30:49.597 --> 00:30:53.226
You've made a lot of money
with us watching your back.

509
00:30:53.309 --> 00:30:56.479
And I know how many customers you have.

510
00:30:56.563 --> 00:30:57.605
What's more.

511
00:30:59.941 --> 00:31:01.568
you're Park Hae-kang.

512
00:31:01.651 --> 00:31:03.152
You can make money out of thin air.

513
00:31:07.574 --> 00:31:10.994
I have nothing left
after greasing everyone's palms.

514
00:31:11.870 --> 00:31:15.456
I should clear things up
with you today. sir.

515
00:31:21.254 --> 00:31:22.714
Do I look like I'm joking right now?

516
00:31:26.467 --> 00:31:28.595
I can show you that I'm not joking.

517
00:31:29.304 --> 00:31:30.263
-Sir.
-Let go of me.

518
00:31:30.346 --> 00:31:31.890
-Sir…
-Let go!

519
00:31:33.641 --> 00:31:34.684
Mr. Son!

520
00:31:41.232 --> 00:31:43.359
What's going on. sir?

521
00:31:43.943 --> 00:31:45.111
He wants ten billion won.

522
00:31:45.612 --> 00:31:46.863
Ten billion won?

523
00:31:52.744 --> 00:31:54.537
Well. this isn't the first time.

524
00:31:55.371 --> 00:31:56.915
It's time to grease some palms.

525
00:31:56.998 --> 00:31:58.166
He must be short on money.

526
00:32:05.506 --> 00:32:06.549
The usual. right?

527
00:32:06.633 --> 00:32:08.134
Yes. Thank you.

528
00:32:08.843 --> 00:32:10.511
-Move aside. please!
-Move!

529
00:32:10.595 --> 00:32:12.180
Excuse me.

530
00:32:13.431 --> 00:32:15.600
I'm an employee here!

531
00:32:15.683 --> 00:32:17.352
I'm telling you. it's my first time here!

532
00:32:17.435 --> 00:32:18.770
Please proceed quietly!

533
00:32:18.853 --> 00:32:19.771
Here's your coffee.

534
00:32:19.854 --> 00:32:21.439
I'm calling my lawyer!

535
00:32:21.522 --> 00:32:23.149
Let go of me!

536
00:32:24.901 --> 00:32:26.778
I just followed someone here!

537
00:32:38.206 --> 00:32:39.040
Please pick up.

538
00:32:39.123 --> 00:32:40.541
MR. SON. SEOUL POLICE CHIEF

539
00:32:48.383 --> 00:32:49.342
This is crazy.

540
00:32:50.259 --> 00:32:51.177
I can't believe this.

541
00:32:52.303 --> 00:32:53.680
Hold on.

542
00:32:53.763 --> 00:32:54.806
What's with him?

543
00:32:54.889 --> 00:32:56.808
Geez.

544
00:32:56.891 --> 00:32:58.434
This place was a gambling den?

545
00:32:58.518 --> 00:33:01.938
Apparently. only people
with top-tier credit ratings got in.

546
00:33:02.522 --> 00:33:04.899
I'll call you back in a minute. sweetie.

547
00:33:04.983 --> 00:33:06.025
Okay.

548
00:33:06.651 --> 00:33:07.902
Are you okay? That jerk!

549
00:33:07.986 --> 00:33:09.362
He hit me!

550
00:33:09.445 --> 00:33:10.655
-Why'd you hit me?
-Are you okay?

551
00:33:11.239 --> 00:33:12.615
-He's beating me up!
-What?

552
00:33:12.699 --> 00:33:14.200
A thug hit me! Call the cops!

553
00:33:14.283 --> 00:33:15.159
-Call the cops!
-Cops!

554
00:33:15.243 --> 00:33:17.120
When did I hit you? I…

555
00:33:17.203 --> 00:33:19.455
-What's going on?
-A thug hit me!

556
00:33:20.206 --> 00:33:21.833
-He's obviously a thug.
-No. I…

557
00:33:21.916 --> 00:33:24.544
All right. I tripped while I was walking…

558
00:33:29.716 --> 00:33:32.468
Sir. you're under arrest for assault.

559
00:33:32.552 --> 00:33:35.763
You have the right to remain silent.
and you have the right to an attorney.

560
00:33:35.847 --> 00:33:37.932
MR. PARK HAE-KANG

561
00:33:45.356 --> 00:33:47.150
We're conducting a Breathalyzer test.

562
00:33:48.568 --> 00:33:50.361
It's 0.09. Your license will be revoked.

563
00:33:50.445 --> 00:33:51.612
-What?
-Please step out.

564
00:33:54.949 --> 00:33:56.451
But I didn't drink!

565
00:33:56.534 --> 00:33:57.994
I can't drink at all.

566
00:33:58.077 --> 00:33:59.412
I can't drink a drop of alcohol.

567
00:33:59.495 --> 00:34:01.205
MR. PARK HAE-KANG

568
00:34:01.289 --> 00:34:02.248
Get in there.

569
00:34:02.331 --> 00:34:03.166
Wait.

570
00:34:04.083 --> 00:34:05.501
Sir. wait.

571
00:34:05.585 --> 00:34:07.545
Why am I in here?

572
00:34:07.628 --> 00:34:10.048
You were reported
for illegally filming women's bodies.

573
00:34:10.131 --> 00:34:12.759
What? Hang on. Illegal filming?

574
00:34:12.842 --> 00:34:15.344
My phone is right here. Look.

575
00:34:15.428 --> 00:34:17.013
All I have are photos of bread!

576
00:34:17.096 --> 00:34:18.639
MR. PARK HAE-KANG

577
00:34:18.723 --> 00:34:19.682
Here. Look.

578
00:34:19.766 --> 00:34:21.267
That's my phone. Wait…

579
00:34:21.350 --> 00:34:22.477
Give it back!

580
00:34:23.061 --> 00:34:24.645
About that issue…

581
00:34:24.729 --> 00:34:27.065
Mr. Park Yong-man
of HK Trading and Investment?

582
00:34:29.192 --> 00:34:30.151
What's this about?

583
00:34:30.234 --> 00:34:31.569
ARREST WARRANT

584
00:34:31.652 --> 00:34:32.653
You need to come with us.

585
00:34:38.493 --> 00:34:42.246
<i>We raided the gambling den.</i>
<i>so we have to bring in the figurehead.</i>

586
00:34:43.039 --> 00:34:44.665
<i>Don't take it too personally.</i>

587
00:35:28.751 --> 00:35:30.837
I've brought everything I could.

588
00:35:45.351 --> 00:35:48.354
I'll take this in return
for releasing your men.

589
00:35:48.938 --> 00:35:50.898
You'll need them to get your work done.

590
00:35:51.524 --> 00:35:52.567
I'll give you three months

591
00:35:53.776 --> 00:35:55.278
for the ten billion I mentioned.

592
00:35:55.820 --> 00:35:57.488
Bring it to me in three months.

593
00:35:58.072 --> 00:35:59.198
And Yong-man?

594
00:36:05.663 --> 00:36:07.415
I need to have some insurance too.

595
00:36:08.124 --> 00:36:11.169
I'll exchange Park Yong-man
for the ten billion.

596
00:36:23.931 --> 00:36:27.810
OUTSTANDING ATHLETE AWARD
PARK HAE-KANG

597
00:36:27.894 --> 00:36:30.396
SPORTS AWARD
PARK HAE-KANG

598
00:36:30.479 --> 00:36:33.816
DAEJUN HIGH SCHOOL
PARK HAE-KANG

599
00:36:40.031 --> 00:36:41.073
Who is it?

600
00:36:45.786 --> 00:36:47.914
What are you doing
in someone else's house?

601
00:36:55.838 --> 00:36:57.048
You must be

602
00:36:57.715 --> 00:36:59.175
Park Hae-kang.

603
00:36:59.884 --> 00:37:00.801
Who are you?

604
00:37:08.017 --> 00:37:09.268
This…

605
00:37:10.561 --> 00:37:14.774
is the loan agreement your father signed
to borrow 30 million won from me.

606
00:37:15.650 --> 00:37:17.902
And you. Park Hae-kang.
are the collateral.

607
00:37:20.071 --> 00:37:21.739
Where is he?

608
00:37:35.962 --> 00:37:37.213
Yes!

609
00:37:37.797 --> 00:37:39.048
What the hell?

610
00:37:39.131 --> 00:37:39.966
What?

611
00:37:40.883 --> 00:37:43.135
You crushed my dream.
and now you're selling me too?

612
00:37:43.219 --> 00:37:44.345
How can you do that to me?

613
00:37:44.428 --> 00:37:45.554
What kind of father are you?

614
00:37:45.638 --> 00:37:48.015
What are you waiting for? Kick him out!

615
00:37:48.099 --> 00:37:51.018
You should manage your business properly!

616
00:37:51.102 --> 00:37:52.395
You little brat!

617
00:37:52.478 --> 00:37:53.604
And he calls himself my son?

618
00:37:53.688 --> 00:37:55.898
How can a father do this to his own child?

619
00:37:55.982 --> 00:37:56.816
Let go of me!

620
00:37:56.899 --> 00:37:58.025
Let go!

621
00:38:00.236 --> 00:38:01.988
Leave while we're asking nicely.

622
00:38:44.405 --> 00:38:45.740
Are you done crying?

623
00:38:49.994 --> 00:38:53.456
I can't do the "I'm your father" thing.

624
00:38:54.332 --> 00:38:58.794
but you can work for me
until you piece your broken dream

625
00:38:59.754 --> 00:39:00.838
back together.

626
00:39:02.631 --> 00:39:03.758
Park Hae-kang.

627
00:39:17.688 --> 00:39:20.149
The food here is amazing.

628
00:39:20.232 --> 00:39:22.735
Perfectly balanced meals…

629
00:39:22.818 --> 00:39:24.236
Just hang in there.

630
00:39:24.737 --> 00:39:26.030
I'll get you out soon.

631
00:39:26.113 --> 00:39:28.699
It's fine. Take your time.

632
00:39:29.450 --> 00:39:31.035
It's not my first time here.

633
00:39:31.744 --> 00:39:33.079
It feels like my old hometown.

634
00:39:39.418 --> 00:39:42.421
Hae-kang. don't strain yourself too hard
to get me out.

635
00:39:43.005 --> 00:39:45.633
I don't have much longer to live anyway.

636
00:39:45.716 --> 00:39:49.470
Find a way to save the others.
They're all relying on you.

637
00:39:50.971 --> 00:39:52.681
Cut the nonsense.

638
00:39:52.765 --> 00:39:56.268
Ever since I took you under my wing
20 years ago.

639
00:39:56.352 --> 00:39:59.188
you've already been
a good enough son to me.

640
00:39:59.855 --> 00:40:02.983
So stop taking care
of other people's lives

641
00:40:03.526 --> 00:40:05.069
and focus on your own.

642
00:40:18.416 --> 00:40:19.250
No.

643
00:40:19.750 --> 00:40:21.168
Don't be ridiculous.

644
00:40:32.847 --> 00:40:34.890
You all went through a lot.

645
00:40:37.685 --> 00:40:38.561
Mr. Park.

646
00:40:40.104 --> 00:40:42.064
Are we just supposed to
take this lying down?

647
00:40:43.274 --> 00:40:45.484
We have enough dirt on Mr. Son too.

648
00:40:46.068 --> 00:40:49.405
It'll be more than enough
to take him down.

649
00:40:49.989 --> 00:40:51.907
He won't stop at Yong-man.

650
00:40:52.533 --> 00:40:53.868
He got to you guys too.

651
00:40:53.951 --> 00:40:56.620
He can easily destroy your lives.

652
00:40:56.704 --> 00:40:58.330
Still. it's ten billion.

653
00:41:00.166 --> 00:41:01.792
Where would we get ten billion won?

654
00:41:02.293 --> 00:41:04.670
We've been extorted
out of over one billion won so far.

655
00:41:04.753 --> 00:41:06.922
But ten billion?

656
00:41:07.506 --> 00:41:09.049
Go live your own lives now.

657
00:41:11.677 --> 00:41:13.554
I'll take care of this.

658
00:41:14.138 --> 00:41:16.015
We're not some gang anyway.

659
00:41:16.682 --> 00:41:18.476
And I'm not your gang leader.

660
00:41:19.059 --> 00:41:20.561
I'm just the CEO.

661
00:41:21.437 --> 00:41:22.897
and you're the employees.

662
00:41:24.023 --> 00:41:25.399
Think of this as quitting.

663
00:41:25.483 --> 00:41:26.525
I'll give you

664
00:41:28.152 --> 00:41:29.904
your severance pay later.

665
00:41:32.948 --> 00:41:34.241
What about our old boss?

666
00:41:35.075 --> 00:41:36.160
What will you do?

667
00:41:37.244 --> 00:41:38.496
He's like a father to me.

668
00:41:38.996 --> 00:41:40.080
I'll take care of him.

669
00:41:42.708 --> 00:41:43.542
Go.

670
00:41:51.091 --> 00:41:52.218
Guys.

671
00:41:54.261 --> 00:41:56.347
Are you sure it's okay to just leave?

672
00:42:07.441 --> 00:42:08.275
Go on.

673
00:42:08.943 --> 00:42:09.902
I'll get going.

674
00:42:11.403 --> 00:42:12.655
Bye. I'll call you.

675
00:42:13.906 --> 00:42:14.907
What are you waiting for?

676
00:42:15.741 --> 00:42:16.742
Bye.

677
00:42:16.825 --> 00:42:18.035
Wait.

678
00:42:22.373 --> 00:42:23.499
Guys.

679
00:42:24.917 --> 00:42:26.168
I'll see you again later.

680
00:42:29.547 --> 00:42:33.509
CHEERS TO YONG-MAN'S NEW BEGINNING!

681
00:42:45.062 --> 00:42:45.938
Sir.

682
00:42:50.317 --> 00:42:51.652
I'm not going to quit.

683
00:42:57.032 --> 00:42:57.950
I won't quit.

684
00:42:59.952 --> 00:43:00.786
Sir…

685
00:43:03.122 --> 00:43:04.081
I…

686
00:43:05.457 --> 00:43:06.667
I'm not quitting either.

687
00:43:07.459 --> 00:43:08.377
What's with you guys?

688
00:43:09.628 --> 00:43:10.879
When Gyeong-buk…

689
00:43:12.881 --> 00:43:14.842
was just an infant.

690
00:43:14.925 --> 00:43:17.803
our boss would change his diapers
and read to him.

691
00:43:18.387 --> 00:43:19.763
He practically raised him.

692
00:43:20.389 --> 00:43:22.099
I couldn't graduate from law school.

693
00:43:22.182 --> 00:43:24.143
but he was the one who secretly paid

694
00:43:24.226 --> 00:43:25.436
for my tuition.

695
00:43:27.021 --> 00:43:28.897
He always praised my cooking

696
00:43:28.981 --> 00:43:30.774
and said I had incredible talent.

697
00:43:30.858 --> 00:43:33.819
He even said
people would line up to try my food

698
00:43:33.902 --> 00:43:35.279
if I opened a restaurant.

699
00:43:35.362 --> 00:43:38.198
He's the one who helped me find my dream.

700
00:43:44.038 --> 00:43:44.997
Mr. Park.

701
00:43:46.582 --> 00:43:47.875
let us help you

702
00:43:49.043 --> 00:43:50.628
save our old boss.

703
00:43:50.711 --> 00:43:52.713
We're not a gang now.

704
00:43:52.796 --> 00:43:55.674
but we're more than just
a CEO and staff. aren't we?

705
00:43:56.675 --> 00:43:57.676
He's right.

706
00:43:58.177 --> 00:44:00.638
We live together. and we die together.

707
00:44:01.138 --> 00:44:02.556
Let us help you!

708
00:44:05.809 --> 00:44:07.561
Are you sure you won't regret it?

709
00:44:08.145 --> 00:44:09.438
-Yes.
-Yes.

710
00:44:13.984 --> 00:44:15.152
Then let's do this.

711
00:44:17.655 --> 00:44:18.489
Ten billion.

712
00:44:19.073 --> 00:44:20.741
I'm sure we'll find a way.

713
00:44:31.960 --> 00:44:34.963
A double-eyelid surgery is quite simple.

714
00:44:35.047 --> 00:44:36.465
so there's no need to be nervous.

715
00:44:36.548 --> 00:44:38.425
Dr. Han. if you don't pay me back.

716
00:44:38.509 --> 00:44:40.344
you might end up
under permanent anesthesia.

717
00:44:41.804 --> 00:44:42.638
COURTHOUSE

718
00:44:42.721 --> 00:44:44.098
Mr. Prosecutor. sir!

719
00:44:44.181 --> 00:44:47.351
The defendant today
was up for habitual illegal gambling.

720
00:44:47.434 --> 00:44:50.854
Can I sue someone for not paying back
their illegal gambling funds?

721
00:44:51.647 --> 00:44:54.525
{\an8}Why has it been so difficult to reach you?

722
00:44:54.608 --> 00:44:55.859
{\an8}YOON JEONG-BOK

723
00:44:56.777 --> 00:44:58.237
You'd better pay up now.

724
00:44:59.655 --> 00:45:01.907
Hello. It's been a while. sir.

725
00:45:01.990 --> 00:45:03.075
Hello.

726
00:45:03.158 --> 00:45:04.368
But who…

727
00:45:09.415 --> 00:45:10.249
Hi there.

728
00:45:14.878 --> 00:45:16.839
This is True Value.

729
00:45:16.922 --> 00:45:19.007
At this price. you got a great deal.

730
00:45:22.052 --> 00:45:25.305
We collected unpaid debts
and even sold my car and apartment.

731
00:45:25.389 --> 00:45:26.849
but this is all we got?

732
00:45:27.433 --> 00:45:29.101
Geez.

733
00:45:31.437 --> 00:45:33.021
A 1st birthday party two weeks ago.

734
00:45:33.105 --> 00:45:37.067
and now Man-sik is having
his 60th birthday party next month.

735
00:45:37.151 --> 00:45:39.653
Who celebrates
their 60th birthday these days?

736
00:45:39.736 --> 00:45:42.156
I know everyone collects money
after retiring. but that jerk…

737
00:45:42.239 --> 00:45:44.116
I mean. he's taken
over 100 million from us.

738
00:45:44.199 --> 00:45:45.200
Hang on.

739
00:45:45.868 --> 00:45:49.288
It was his kid's 1st birthday.
and he's turning 60 next month?

740
00:45:49.955 --> 00:45:51.415
He had a kid at 59 years old?

741
00:45:52.583 --> 00:45:54.042
Did you hear anything

742
00:45:54.126 --> 00:45:56.253
about how much he collected
at the birthday party?

743
00:45:56.336 --> 00:45:57.421
I'm not sure how much.

744
00:45:57.504 --> 00:46:00.424
but I heard he bought an apartment
after the party.

745
00:46:00.507 --> 00:46:02.092
An apartment? Where?

746
00:46:02.176 --> 00:46:03.969
-In Gangnam?
-Yes.

747
00:46:07.097 --> 00:46:08.390
We should host something too.

748
00:46:09.183 --> 00:46:11.894
-Host something?
-We've been giving out money.

749
00:46:11.977 --> 00:46:13.437
I bet it's at least 600 million.

750
00:46:13.520 --> 00:46:14.897
We'll gain it all back this time.

751
00:46:15.606 --> 00:46:16.690
What kind of event?

752
00:46:17.274 --> 00:46:18.275
A wedding!

753
00:46:18.358 --> 00:46:20.861
Wouldn't weddings bring in
the most cash gifts?

754
00:46:20.944 --> 00:46:22.362
That's a good idea.

755
00:46:22.446 --> 00:46:24.448
But we don't have a bride.

756
00:46:26.158 --> 00:46:27.618
How may I help you. ma'am?

757
00:46:31.371 --> 00:46:33.832
WEE PARTNERS
FREE LEGAL CONSULTATION APPLICATION

758
00:46:33.916 --> 00:46:36.460
My son's dead.

759
00:46:37.669 --> 00:46:39.254
People keep telling me

760
00:46:39.338 --> 00:46:42.883
I have to renounce the inheritance
or something.

761
00:46:42.966 --> 00:46:45.636
but I don't have the money
to hire a lawyer.

762
00:46:47.054 --> 00:46:48.514
You came to the right place.

763
00:46:48.597 --> 00:46:51.266
We're here to help people like you.

764
00:46:53.143 --> 00:46:55.312
-You filed the death report. right?
-Yes.

765
00:46:55.896 --> 00:46:57.606
Take these files.

766
00:46:58.857 --> 00:47:00.526
Thank you so much.

767
00:47:00.609 --> 00:47:02.486
Of course. I get paid to do this.

768
00:47:05.239 --> 00:47:06.114
Ms. Kang.

769
00:47:06.865 --> 00:47:07.783
Yes?

770
00:47:08.742 --> 00:47:09.576
Well…

771
00:47:10.410 --> 00:47:13.205
Don't you know we send up customers
for cases like that?

772
00:47:13.705 --> 00:47:16.291
It should've been a paid case.

773
00:47:18.210 --> 00:47:19.169
YEONG-JU

774
00:47:19.253 --> 00:47:22.047
She didn't have much money.

775
00:47:24.091 --> 00:47:26.093
You're unbelievable.

776
00:47:33.141 --> 00:47:35.227
-What?
-Are you free this weekend?

777
00:47:35.310 --> 00:47:36.311
There's a gig for you.

778
00:47:36.895 --> 00:47:39.481
-What is it?
-Can you afford to be picky right now?

779
00:47:39.565 --> 00:47:41.149
You need to send money to your sister.

780
00:47:43.527 --> 00:47:44.403
Deal.

781
00:47:50.033 --> 00:47:52.035
WARMEST CONGRATULATIONS
ON YOUR BEAUTIFUL UNION

782
00:47:52.619 --> 00:47:53.870
-Hello!
-Hello!

783
00:47:56.206 --> 00:47:58.250
-I'm here.
-Hey.

784
00:48:03.797 --> 00:48:05.257
He's here.

785
00:48:06.883 --> 00:48:07.718
Wow.

786
00:48:07.801 --> 00:48:09.886
Am I in a crime movie or what?

787
00:48:09.970 --> 00:48:11.430
Who's getting married?

788
00:48:12.306 --> 00:48:13.765
WE'RE GETTING MARRIED

789
00:48:13.849 --> 00:48:14.933
GROOM
PARK HAE-KANG

790
00:48:15.017 --> 00:48:16.310
PARK HAE-KANG & KIM MIN-JI

791
00:48:16.393 --> 00:48:17.769
CONGRATULATIONS. HAE-KANG

792
00:48:17.853 --> 00:48:20.772
YOUR BROTHER. TADAYOSHI

793
00:48:22.649 --> 00:48:23.525
Boss!

794
00:48:34.244 --> 00:48:35.912
-Move over for a bit.
-What?

795
00:48:37.080 --> 00:48:38.332
Do I have to go this far?

796
00:48:40.459 --> 00:48:42.127
One of you can do it. Why me?

797
00:48:43.920 --> 00:48:45.005
We already told you.

798
00:48:45.088 --> 00:48:47.007
We'll get more cash if you're the groom.

799
00:48:47.090 --> 00:48:48.425
Wow.

800
00:48:48.508 --> 00:48:49.509
You look so handsome.

801
00:48:49.593 --> 00:48:50.636
Your lips are very nice.

802
00:48:50.719 --> 00:48:53.347
He's the most handsome customer
you've had. isn't he?

803
00:48:53.430 --> 00:48:54.389
See?

804
00:48:55.599 --> 00:48:56.600
Mr. Park!

805
00:48:57.893 --> 00:49:01.063
All our retired members are here.

806
00:49:01.146 --> 00:49:03.649
The venue's filled with guests!

807
00:49:03.732 --> 00:49:06.026
But we're already out of beef tartare.

808
00:49:08.987 --> 00:49:10.614
Is the bride here?

809
00:49:15.994 --> 00:49:16.828
Me?

810
00:49:17.496 --> 00:49:18.997
I'm getting married today?

811
00:49:19.081 --> 00:49:20.916
That's what I'm telling you.

812
00:49:20.999 --> 00:49:22.459
Hurry up and change.

813
00:49:22.542 --> 00:49:24.044
You need to get your makeup done.

814
00:49:24.544 --> 00:49:26.797
There must be some kind of mistake.

815
00:49:26.880 --> 00:49:28.715
I thought I was going to be a guest.

816
00:49:28.799 --> 00:49:30.717
I'm sorry. I can't do this.

817
00:49:30.801 --> 00:49:32.928
I heard you were referred by Yeong-ju.

818
00:49:33.011 --> 00:49:34.554
You can't back out now.

819
00:49:34.638 --> 00:49:37.391
How would we find
another bride last-minute?

820
00:49:39.226 --> 00:49:41.853
-I'll pay you generously.
-Ma'am.

821
00:49:41.937 --> 00:49:45.440
Didn't you see those men out there?
They look like thugs.

822
00:49:45.524 --> 00:49:48.527
The groom must be someone
in the underworld.

823
00:49:49.319 --> 00:49:50.237
I'm sorry.

824
00:49:51.822 --> 00:49:54.408
Hey. you can't just leave now!

825
00:49:54.491 --> 00:49:56.159
We don't have time.

826
00:49:58.453 --> 00:49:59.746
Five million won.

827
00:50:04.960 --> 00:50:05.961
Deal.

828
00:50:18.056 --> 00:50:20.642
The wedding of Park Hae-kang

829
00:50:20.726 --> 00:50:22.269
and Kim Min-ji will begin shortly…

830
00:50:22.352 --> 00:50:25.480
I know this must be overwhelming.
but I'm counting on you.

831
00:50:27.649 --> 00:50:30.318
In any case. let's do this.

832
00:50:33.864 --> 00:50:34.990
Hold on tight.

833
00:50:35.073 --> 00:50:36.700
…let us meet the bride and groom.

834
00:50:36.783 --> 00:50:39.202
Please welcome them
with a big round of applause.

835
00:50:39.995 --> 00:50:42.289
The bride and groom will now enter.

836
00:51:12.235 --> 00:51:14.738
-Park Hae-kang!
-Park Hae-kang!

837
00:51:14.821 --> 00:51:18.116
-Park Hae-kang!
-Park Hae-kang!

838
00:51:18.200 --> 00:51:20.744
-Park Hae-kang!
-Park Hae-kang!

839
00:51:20.827 --> 00:51:23.997
-Park Hae-kang!
-Park Hae-kang!

840
00:51:24.080 --> 00:51:27.250
-Park Hae-kang!
-Park Hae-kang!

841
00:51:27.334 --> 00:51:30.170
-Park Hae-kang!
-Park Hae-kang!

842
00:51:40.597 --> 00:51:43.475
Sharing a life as husband and wife

843
00:51:45.227 --> 00:51:49.648
is not easy. of course.

844
00:51:49.731 --> 00:51:51.399
but if you live as each other's half

845
00:51:51.483 --> 00:51:54.402
and live faithfully together.

846
00:51:54.986 --> 00:51:55.946
you'll…

847
00:51:59.407 --> 00:52:00.659
Live happily together.

848
00:52:07.749 --> 00:52:12.212
Next. to celebrate this joyful union.

849
00:52:12.295 --> 00:52:15.257
the groom's colleagues have prepared

850
00:52:15.340 --> 00:52:17.008
a special performance.

851
00:52:17.676 --> 00:52:19.553
Please welcome them
with a round of applause.

852
00:52:24.683 --> 00:52:28.728
<i>We're going to smile. smile again</i>

853
00:52:28.812 --> 00:52:32.148
<i>This is a happy moment. happy day</i>

854
00:52:32.232 --> 00:52:34.359
<i>Straighten your shoulders</i>

855
00:52:34.442 --> 00:52:39.197
<i>And erase all your worries</i>

856
00:52:39.281 --> 00:52:42.492
<i>Forget your sadness. never cry</i>

857
00:52:42.576 --> 00:52:45.704
<i>Beneath the blazing sun. sunny day</i>

858
00:52:46.288 --> 00:52:50.166
<i>Just wish for only good things</i>

859
00:52:50.250 --> 00:52:52.377
<i>To come your way</i>

860
00:53:00.135 --> 00:53:03.930
<i>Like the vast sky. laugh louder</i>

861
00:53:04.014 --> 00:53:07.434
<i>And think bigger</i>

862
00:53:07.517 --> 00:53:10.645
<i>Forget your tears. never cry</i>

863
00:53:10.729 --> 00:53:13.607
<i>Like the bright sunlight. sunshine day</i>

864
00:53:13.690 --> 00:53:19.487
<i>I'll pray that your days</i>
<i>Will be filled with happiness</i>

865
00:53:19.571 --> 00:53:20.780
Park Hae-kang!

866
00:53:20.864 --> 00:53:22.741
Congratulations. Park Hae-kang!

867
00:53:22.824 --> 00:53:24.618
Picture-perfect. Park Hae-kang!

868
00:53:32.083 --> 00:53:33.793
All right.

869
00:53:33.877 --> 00:53:36.630
Then lastly. why don't the bride and groom

870
00:53:36.713 --> 00:53:38.673
kiss for the photo?

871
00:53:43.511 --> 00:53:47.641
-Kiss! Kiss!
-Kiss! Kiss!

872
00:53:47.724 --> 00:53:49.517
Mr. Park. you have to kiss!

873
00:53:49.601 --> 00:53:53.271
-Kiss! Kiss!
-Kiss! Kiss!

874
00:53:53.355 --> 00:53:56.858
-Kiss! Kiss!
-Kiss! Kiss!

875
00:53:56.942 --> 00:54:00.028
-Kiss! Kiss!
-Kiss! Kiss!

876
00:54:00.111 --> 00:54:01.655
-Kiss! Kiss!
-Kiss! Kiss!

877
00:54:01.738 --> 00:54:03.073
Two million more.

878
00:54:03.156 --> 00:54:07.202
-Kiss! Kiss!
-Kiss! Kiss!

879
00:54:29.849 --> 00:54:30.725
It's okay.

880
00:54:31.893 --> 00:54:33.186
I got paid more.

881
00:54:34.145 --> 00:54:35.146
So it's fine.

882
00:54:50.870 --> 00:54:52.372
Is it the right amount?

883
00:54:52.455 --> 00:54:54.624
Two million extra for the kiss.

884
00:54:54.708 --> 00:54:56.084
Yes. Everything's in there.

885
00:54:56.167 --> 00:54:59.129
But it wasn't a proper kiss.

886
00:54:59.754 --> 00:55:00.588
What?

887
00:55:00.672 --> 00:55:01.965
The kiss.

888
00:55:02.048 --> 00:55:05.593
I only kissed my thumb.
and it was next to your lips.

889
00:55:12.267 --> 00:55:14.519
Still. we touched.

890
00:55:14.602 --> 00:55:16.396
Do you even know how I feel?

891
00:55:16.896 --> 00:55:17.897
I paid a fair. I mean…

892
00:55:18.481 --> 00:55:21.776
I paid you plenty for that.
Should I worry about your feelings too?

893
00:55:21.860 --> 00:55:25.196
You hired a fake bride
and held a grand wedding.

894
00:55:25.280 --> 00:55:27.198
I feel like I'm involved
in some huge scam.

895
00:55:27.282 --> 00:55:29.034
It just feels wrong.

896
00:55:29.117 --> 00:55:31.161
What's more. there's this…

897
00:55:31.244 --> 00:55:32.829
There was some touching involved.

898
00:55:32.912 --> 00:55:35.040
Well. you were the one who said.

899
00:55:35.123 --> 00:55:38.376
"Deal."

900
00:55:38.460 --> 00:55:40.503
You said it so willingly.

901
00:55:41.796 --> 00:55:42.714
Anyway.

902
00:55:43.256 --> 00:55:46.384
this was unpleasant for both of us.
so let's not cross paths again.

903
00:55:51.222 --> 00:55:53.683
As someone working in law.
let me tell you something.

904
00:55:53.767 --> 00:55:56.352
Stay on the right side of the law.

905
00:56:05.361 --> 00:56:07.322
Let's just focus on helping Yong-man.

906
00:56:08.406 --> 00:56:09.324
Focus.

907
00:56:12.994 --> 00:56:14.287
We're still 6.5 billion short.

908
00:56:14.370 --> 00:56:15.705
Is there anything else?

909
00:56:15.789 --> 00:56:18.374
There's only the Lizard
to collect from. but…

910
00:56:18.458 --> 00:56:20.376
Luck is on my side today.

911
00:56:20.460 --> 00:56:21.294
Thanks.

912
00:56:22.128 --> 00:56:24.631
-But what?
-I visited his management office.

913
00:56:24.714 --> 00:56:26.174
but they said he's currently wanted.

914
00:56:26.674 --> 00:56:27.842
Wanted? For what?

915
00:56:27.926 --> 00:56:29.511
Embezzlement and breach of trust.

916
00:56:30.345 --> 00:56:32.138
Find him before the police do.

917
00:56:32.222 --> 00:56:34.808
Tell him to pay me back
with the money he embezzled.

918
00:56:35.600 --> 00:56:36.893
I just got the Lizard's location.

919
00:56:39.104 --> 00:56:40.146
He's in Osan.

920
00:56:40.730 --> 00:56:42.232
Get him. Now.

921
00:56:57.831 --> 00:56:59.541
I'll pay you back! Please!

922
00:56:59.624 --> 00:57:01.084
Please don't kill me!

923
00:57:06.464 --> 00:57:08.049
Mr. Park is here.

924
00:57:08.133 --> 00:57:09.467
Sir!

925
00:57:09.551 --> 00:57:10.844
Mr. Park!

926
00:57:10.927 --> 00:57:12.887
What took you so long?

927
00:57:12.971 --> 00:57:14.556
Tell them to let me go.

928
00:57:14.639 --> 00:57:16.015
I'm freezing right now.

929
00:57:16.099 --> 00:57:18.226
-Please. help me!
-What about my money?

930
00:57:18.309 --> 00:57:20.812
We retrieved 20 million.
and we checked his credit rating.

931
00:57:20.895 --> 00:57:22.147
It's Grade 8.

932
00:57:22.230 --> 00:57:23.690
Then he can't pay me back.

933
00:57:30.655 --> 00:57:32.240
You assholes!

934
00:57:32.323 --> 00:57:34.159
Are you a bunch of thugs or what?

935
00:57:34.826 --> 00:57:38.705
You're just lowlifes earning petty cash
from a gambling den!

936
00:57:38.788 --> 00:57:40.373
You can't kill anyone!

937
00:57:40.457 --> 00:57:42.167
Come on. then! Kill me!

938
00:57:42.750 --> 00:57:44.544
Get on with it! I'm freezing!

939
00:57:44.627 --> 00:57:47.213
-I'll either freeze to death or fall!
-Level 2!

940
00:57:47.297 --> 00:57:48.214
Just try…

941
00:57:50.467 --> 00:57:51.759
Help me!

942
00:57:51.843 --> 00:57:53.428
Help me! I'm sorry!

943
00:57:53.511 --> 00:57:54.846
I'm sorry!

944
00:57:55.889 --> 00:57:56.973
I'm sorry.

945
00:57:57.849 --> 00:58:00.226
I won't act up. I swear.

946
00:58:15.116 --> 00:58:15.992
Mr. Park.

947
00:58:16.993 --> 00:58:18.578
Are there about 10.000 households here?

948
00:58:21.998 --> 00:58:22.957
What?

949
00:58:23.458 --> 00:58:25.210
This apartment complex!

950
00:58:26.753 --> 00:58:28.379
Are there about 10.000 households?

951
00:58:29.339 --> 00:58:30.465
There are 9.800.

952
00:58:35.386 --> 00:58:37.222
I saw on my way here

953
00:58:37.305 --> 00:58:40.683
that your apartment complex is having
a building representative election.

954
00:58:40.767 --> 00:58:42.560
I have a great idea.

955
00:58:42.644 --> 00:58:43.645
Just hear me out.

956
00:58:43.728 --> 00:58:44.729
Get rid of him.

957
00:58:44.812 --> 00:58:47.690
-Just throw him off. Let's go.
-Wait!

958
00:58:47.774 --> 00:58:49.484
There's easy money

959
00:58:49.984 --> 00:58:53.029
in this apartment complex
that you don't know about!

960
00:58:54.489 --> 00:58:55.907
Check my jacket.

961
00:58:55.990 --> 00:58:58.785
There's a notebook
and some account books in my pocket.

962
00:58:58.868 --> 00:59:00.495
You'll believe me once you see it.

963
00:59:19.931 --> 00:59:20.765
Let him go for now.

964
00:59:21.933 --> 00:59:22.976
Thank you.

965
00:59:25.895 --> 00:59:27.438
It's the other way.

966
00:59:32.402 --> 00:59:35.405
Isn't this going a bit too far
for a prank?

967
00:59:36.322 --> 00:59:37.615
What is this?

968
00:59:42.078 --> 00:59:44.247
Records of what I've been skimming off.

969
00:59:44.789 --> 00:59:47.959
I inflated the maintenance fees
and procurement costs

970
00:59:48.543 --> 00:59:51.004
and received payments
from bidding competitors.

971
00:59:52.880 --> 00:59:54.632
I gambled with money from all that.

972
00:59:55.216 --> 00:59:57.135
So this is proof that you're trash…

973
00:59:58.428 --> 01:00:01.222
I can pay back everything
if I just work for a week

974
01:00:01.306 --> 01:00:02.932
<i>at my apartment complex.</i>

975
01:00:05.935 --> 01:00:07.020
{\an8}PLUMBING MATERIALS

976
01:00:07.103 --> 01:00:08.271
{\an8}ELECTRICAL SUPPLIES

977
01:00:08.354 --> 01:00:09.314
{\an8}CHRISTMAS EVENT

978
01:00:09.397 --> 01:00:10.398
{\an8}EXTERIOR WALL CONSTRUCTION

979
01:00:10.481 --> 01:00:12.108
{\an8}MAINTENANCE FEES. SECURITY SERVICE…

980
01:00:15.111 --> 01:00:16.195
{\an8}SENIOR CENTER REMODELING

981
01:00:16.279 --> 01:00:18.114
{\an8}SUPPLIES ORGANIZATION. LANDSCAPING…

982
01:00:19.699 --> 01:00:20.575
Four billion?

983
01:00:22.577 --> 01:00:24.412
You pocketed four billion won?

984
01:00:24.996 --> 01:00:26.998
Our apartment complex
only has 1.200 households.

985
01:00:27.582 --> 01:00:29.334
and I skimmed that much.

986
01:00:29.417 --> 01:00:30.335
But this place

987
01:00:30.835 --> 01:00:33.963
has almost 10.000 households.

988
01:00:34.047 --> 01:00:36.841
Then how much do you think
you can skim off?

989
01:00:37.550 --> 01:00:39.218
A billion? Two billion?

990
01:00:39.302 --> 01:00:41.721
That's pocket change!

991
01:00:42.305 --> 01:00:44.015
You could even skim off ten billion!

992
01:00:47.143 --> 01:00:49.437
I'm serious. Mr. Park!

993
01:00:50.146 --> 01:00:51.105
Ten billion?

994
01:00:51.189 --> 01:00:52.190
Yes.

995
01:01:26.099 --> 01:01:27.517
We can skim off

996
01:01:28.976 --> 01:01:30.269
ten billion won

997
01:01:31.062 --> 01:01:32.563
from this apartment complex?

998
01:01:38.403 --> 01:01:40.321
THE APARTMENT JOB

999
01:02:04.470 --> 01:02:06.597
<i>How do we skim off ten billion then?</i>

1000
01:02:06.681 --> 01:02:09.934
{\an8}<i>Become the building representative.</i>
<i>then the president.</i>

1001
01:02:10.017 --> 01:02:11.561
{\an8}<i>Would there really be ten billion here?</i>

1002
01:02:11.644 --> 01:02:14.272
{\an8}Ask them how much
the long-term repair reserve fund is.

1003
01:02:14.355 --> 01:02:15.189
{\an8}Long-term what?

1004
01:02:15.273 --> 01:02:18.192
{\an8}<i>There's 17.857.420.000 won.</i>

1005
01:02:18.276 --> 01:02:19.694
{\an8}<i>The complex residents</i>
<i>aren't doing anything?</i>

1006
01:02:19.777 --> 01:02:23.197
{\an8}<i>Everyone's busy with their own lives.</i>
<i>They don't even care about it.</i>

1007
01:02:23.281 --> 01:02:25.241
{\an8}<i>-You have to run for building rep.</i>
<i>-Do you live alone?</i>

1008
01:02:25.324 --> 01:02:27.910
{\an8}I've never seen anyone living alone
run for building representative.

1009
01:02:27.994 --> 01:02:30.872
{\an8}<i>We need a family</i>
<i>to take that repair reserve fund.</i>

1010
01:02:30.955 --> 01:02:32.665
{\an8}<i>Mom. Dad. Grandma. Grandpa.</i>
<i>People like that.</i>

1011
01:02:32.749 --> 01:02:33.958
{\an8}<i>Let's work on something together.</i>

1012
01:02:34.041 --> 01:02:35.752
{\an8}<i>Play the role of my wife for three months.</i>

1013
01:02:35.835 --> 01:02:37.670
{\an8}<i>-Play the role of what?</i>
<i>-My wife.</i>

1014
01:02:37.754 --> 01:02:38.671
{\an8}A hundred million.

1015
01:02:38.755 --> 01:02:40.381
{\an8}A hundred million for three months.

1016
01:02:43.509 --> 01:02:45.511
Subtitle translation by: Juyoung Park

1017
